author: Sam Barsanti
title: Newswire: Diego Luna and Vicente Fox will join Conan’s big Mexico trip
text:
Share Tweet 
Last month , Conan O’Brien announced on his Conan show that he would be going to Mexico in March for a special Mexico-centric episode with Mexican guests, a Mexican audience, and an all-Mexican crew working on the show. Tonight, O’Brien announced two of the guests he’ll be speaking with: Rogue One ‘s Diego Luna and former President Of Mexico Vicente Fox, who you may remember as the guy who recently tweeted this: I’ve made it clear, Mexico is not paying for that #FuckingWall . US Congress don’t get fooled by @realDonaldTrump . You can stop his maddness. — Vicente Fox Quesada (@VicenteFoxQue) February 3, 2017 
So that’ll be fun. The special is called “Conan Without Borders: Made In Mexico,” and it will air on March 1. You can see a video of O’Brien announcing the guests below.
